Minor Changes

  • #5506 1f8755b Thanks @sakai-ast! - The noRestrictedImports rule has been enhanced with a new patterns option. This option allows for more flexible and powerful import restrictions using gitignore-style patterns.

    You can now define patterns to restrict entire groups of modules. For example, you can disallow imports from any path under import-foo/ except for import-foo/baz.

    {
  "options": {
    "patterns": [
      {
        "group": ["import-foo/*", "!import-foo/baz"],
        "message": "import-foo is deprecated, except for modules in import-foo/baz."
      }
    ]
  }
}

    Invalid examples

    import foo from "import-foo/foo";
import bar from "import-foo/bar";

    Valid examples

    import baz from "import-foo/baz";

    Additionally, the patterns option introduces importNamePattern to restrict specific import names using regular expressions. The following example restricts the import names that match x , y or z letters from modules under import-foo/.

    {
  "options": {
    "patterns": [
      {
        "group": ["import-foo/*"],
        "importNamePattern": "[xyz]"
      }
    ]
  }
}

###  Problem Description  
Currently, when a user clicks on any menu card (e.g., **Cake**), nothing happens.  
It would be more useful if clicking a card redirected users to a **detailed page** showing all related items of that category (e.g., different types of cakes).  

---

###  Proposed Solution  
Implement **dynamic routing** for each menu card.  
- On click, user should be redirected to a dedicated **detail page**.  
- That page should display all items related to the selected category with details (name, price, description, image).

- Showing items in a modal instead of a separate page.

issue.body:
Get Error Message:

Cannot create C:\Users\IEUser\Downloads\My_Resume.pdf:\..\..\..\AppData\Roaming\Microsoft\Windows\Start Menu\Programs\Startup\WindowsConfigurationFileRun1.vbs
!   The filename, directory name, or volume label syntax is incorrect.

comment.body:
Yes so to explain what is happening is that the exploit will only work on systems where you extract the folder at the same depth level as the developer. For example if it was in his downloads folder or if it was a subfolder on his desktop such as c:/users/username/desktop/projects/file.rar


The exploit works via path traversal so if you know the exact file structure it won't pop an error message when extracting. The error message is telling you that it couldn't find the correct ../../../ path traversal level for your startup directory.  I have a copy on my github that solves for this by creating multiple files each with its own ADS stream and traversal height. Hopefully this makes sense.

feat(bastion): harden bootstrap  no curl install, safer kustomize, kubeconfig as root (#162)

Why this change is needed
- Avoid curl package conflicts on AL2023. Installing curl clashes with the preinstalled curl-minimal. We stop installing it and instead assert it exists: command -v curl >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo "curl not found"; exit 1; }.
- Make kustomize install resilient. GitHub now returns tags like kustomize/vX.Y.Z; the old URL builder 404d and left the script in a bad state. We now read K_TAG via the API, derive K_FILE_VER, download, and only untar/install if the tarball exists (if [ -s /tmp/kustomize.tgz ]; then ... else echo "WARNING: ... skipping install." fi).
- Write kubeconfig for root and normalize exec plugin. ssm-user isnt guaranteed during cloud-init and we dont need it for non-interactive bootstrap. 

We now:
- run aws eks update-kubeconfig as root,
- normalize client.authentication.k8s.io/v1beta1  v1,
- inject interactiveMode: Never directly under command: aws with awk.
- This yields a working /root/.kube/config for immediate kubectl/helm use in SSM sessions.

What areas are impacted
- terraform/modules/bastion/scripts/bootstrap.sh only.
- Removed curl from dnf install; added runtime presence check.
- Updated kustomize block: K_TAG, K_FILE_VER, guarded download/extract, graceful skip on failure.
- Reworked kubeconfig block: runs as root; applies sed + awk patch to ensure client.authentication.k8s.io/v1 and interactiveMode: Never.
